title: Art & Expression Workshop
description:
Art & Expression Workshop: Create. Connect. Come Alive.

Event Overview

Whether your canvas is a wall, a page, or your own voice — this is your space to break free and express. The Art & Expression Workshop is a safe and inspiring environment to explore creativity through different mediums, channel emotions into form, and connect with others through raw, authentic expression.

Key Highlights

  • Multimedia Creation Zones: Paint, draw, write, collage, or sculpt — choose your outlet and unleash your flow.
  • Spoken Word & Open Mic: Share your thoughts, poetry, and stories with a supportive audience.
  • Emotion through Motion: Movement-based expression through guided dance and body language workshops.
  • Collaborative Murals: Co-create large art pieces that represent group emotions, messages, or dreams.
  • Mindful Art Practices: Learn how art can be a tool for healing, self-reflection, and mental clarity.

Why Attend?

  • Rediscover the joy of unfiltered creativity, regardless of skill level.
  • Connect deeply with yourself and others through shared expression.
  • Explore the intersection of art, emotion, and identity in a non-judgmental space.
  • Leave with your own art, a lighter heart, and a clearer voice.
location: Pokhara Art Gallery, Baidam Rd, Lakeside-6, Pokhara 33700, Nepal

title: Midnight Brew Fest
description:
Midnight Brew Fest: Where Coffee Meets Creativity

Event Overview

When the sun sets and the stars rise, the brews begin to flow. Midnight Brew Fest is a nocturnal celebration of coffee culture, creativity, and good vibes. Join fellow night owls for a sensory experience full of artisanal blends, ambient music, spontaneous art, and cozy conversations — all fueled by the perfect cup.

Key Highlights

  • Brew Battles: Baristas go head-to-head in a live showdown of espresso artistry and latte flair.
  • Tasting Trails: Sample unique blends, cold brews, nitro infusions, and rare roasts from local and global bean crafters.
  • Live Acoustic & Lo-Fi Sets: Let the mellow rhythms of live music accompany your midnight sips.
  • Coffee & Canvas: Unwind with paint and a pour — create your masterpiece in a guided open-air session.
  • After-Hours Conversations: Lounge in our chill corners and spark deep talks over steamy mugs and starry skies.

Why Attend?

  • Fuel your inner night owl with world-class brews and bold flavors.
  • Connect with fellow creatives, caffeine lovers, and dreamers.
  • Experience the perfect blend of chill vibes, art, and aroma — all after dark.
  • Take home exclusive blends and barista tips to elevate your coffee game.
location: Sydney, Australia

title: Robotics Expo
description:
Exhibit and Interact with Real Robotic Prototypes

Event Overview

Discover the future of robotics at this hands-on event showcasing cutting-edge robotic prototypes. Engage with innovative designs, interact with creators, and experience the latest advancements in robotics technology.

Key Highlights

  • Live Demonstrations: Witness robotic prototypes in action, from autonomous drones to humanoid assistants.
  • Interactive Sessions: Get hands-on with select prototypes and explore their functionalities.
  • Meet the Innovators: Connect with engineers and designers to learn about the development process.
  • Technology Showcase: Discover real-world applications in healthcare, manufacturing, and more.

Why Attend?

  • Gain insights into the future of automation and AI-driven robotics.
  • Network with industry professionals and enthusiasts.
  • Experience the thrill of interacting with next-gen technology.
location: Biratnagar Engineering College Auditorium, Tinpaini Road, Biratnagar 56613, Nepal

title: Photography Walk
description:
Explore the World Through Your Lens: Photography Walk

Event Overview

Join fellow photography enthusiasts for a guided walk through scenic locations, where every corner becomes a canvas for creativity. Whether you're using a DSLR, smartphone, or film camera, this event is designed to inspire and help you see the world with fresh perspective.

Key Highlights

  • Curated Routes: Walk through handpicked spots known for their visual charm and storytelling potential.
  • Mentor Guidance: Learn tips and tricks from experienced photographers at every stop.
  • Theme-Based Shooting: Challenge yourself with themes like street life, architecture, portraits, and nature.
  • Community Interaction: Share your shots, exchange ideas, and grow your creative network.

Why Attend?

  • Sharpen your photography skills in real-world scenarios.
  • Discover hidden gems in your city or town through a creative lens.
  • Be part of a vibrant, supportive photography community.
  • Receive feedback and insights to improve your craft.
location: Meet at Basundhara Park Gate, Lakeside Rd, Pokhara 33700, Nepal
